title: The Golden Silence
creator: C.N and A.M. Williamson
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Golden Silence, by Charles Norris Williamson and Alice Muriel Williamson. Trying to get away from an engagement he had got himself into more or less against his will, Stephen Knight travels to Algiers to visit his old friend Nevill. On the Journey there he meets the charming and beautiful Victoria. She is on her way to Algiers to search for her sister, who had disappeared years ago after marrying an Arab nobleman. With the support of his friend, Stephen Knight decides to help the girl - but when she also disappears, the adventure begins... (Summary by Carolin) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; desert; africa; kidnapping

reviews.reviewbody: This story starts out a bit slow but picks up the pace very quickly.  It has romance, adventure and intrigue in it.  I enjoyed the story and the narration was good.  Some different narrators but Jules Hawryluk narrated most of it and he has a really nice tone to his voice.  Please keep up the good work Jules!  Be warned there are some very racially insensitive words used in this story, unfortunately, I am sure in the 1800's they were used.
